{"identifier":{"url":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable"],"title":"Guided generation","anchor":"Guided-generation"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"Generating Swift data structures with guided generation","modules":[{"name":"Foundation Models"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you perform a request, the model returns a raw string in its natural language"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"format. Raw strings require you to manually parse the details you want. Instead of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"working with raw strings, the framework provides guided generation, which gives","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"strong guarantees that the response is in a format you expect."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To use guided generation, describe the output you want as a new Swift type.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"When you make a request to the model, include your custom type and the framework","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"performs the work necessary to fill in and return an object with the parameters filled","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"in for you. The framework uses constrained sampling when generating output, which defines","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the rules on what the model can generate. Constrained sampling prevents the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"model from producing malformed output and provides you with results as a type you define.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For more information about creating a session and prompting the model, see"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/generating-content-and-performing-tasks-with-foundation-models","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Conform-your-data-type-to-Generable","level":2,"text":"Conform your data type to Generable"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To conform your type to "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable"},{"text":", describe the type and the parameters to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"guide the response of the model. The framework supports generating"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"content with basic Swift types like ","type":"text"},{"code":"Bool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Int","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Float"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"Double","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"Decimal","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and ","type":"text"},{"code":"Array","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". For example, if you only want the model to return a numeric result, call","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession/respond(to:generating:includeSchemaInPrompt:options:)-13kji","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using the type "},{"code":"Float","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["let prompt = \"How many tablespoons are in a cup?\"","let session = LanguageModelSession(model: .default)","","// Generate a response with the type `Float`, instead of `String`.","let response = try await session.respond(to: prompt, generating: Float.self)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A schema provides the ability to control the values of a property, and you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"specify guides to control values you associate with it. The framework provides two","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"macros that help you with schema creation. Use "},{"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Generable(description:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":""},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on structures, actors, and enumerations; and only use ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/Guide(description:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stored properties."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When you add descriptions to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"text":" properties, you help the model understand","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the semantics of the properties. Keep the descriptions as short as possible — long","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"descriptions take up additional context size and can introduce latency. The following"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"example creates a type that describes a cat and includes a name, an age that’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"constrained to a range of values, and a short profile:"}]},{"code":["@Generable(description: \"Basic profile information about a cat\")","struct CatProfile {","    // A guide isn't necessary for basic fields.","    var name: String","","    @Guide(description: \"The age of the cat\", .range(0...20))","    var age: Int","","    @Guide(description: \"A one sentence profile about the cat's personality\")","    var profile: String","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The model generates "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"type":"text","text":" properties in the order they’re declared."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can nest custom ","type":"text"},{"code":"Generable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" types inside other "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"text":" types, and mark","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"enumerations with associated values as ","type":"text"},{"code":"Generable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"type":"text","text":" macro ensures"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that all associated and nested values are themselves generable. This allows for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"advanced use cases like creating complex data types or dynamically generating"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"views at runtime."}]},{"text":"Make a request with your custom data type","type":"heading","anchor":"Make-a-request-with-your-custom-data-type","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After creating your type, use it along with a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/LanguageModelSession"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to prompt the model. When you use a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Generable"},{"text":" type it prevents the model","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from producing malformed output and prevents the need for any manual string","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"parsing."}]},{"code":["// Generate a response using a custom type.","let response = try await session.respond(","    to: \"Generate a cute rescue cat\",","    generating: CatProfile.self",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"heading","text":"Define a dynamic schema at runtime","level":2,"anchor":"Define-a-dynamic-schema-at-runtime"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you don’t know what you want the model to produce at compile time use"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/DynamicGenerationSchema"},{"type":"text","text":" to define what you need. For example,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"when you’re working on a restaurant app and want to restrict the model to pick"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from menu options that a restaurant provides. Because each restaurant provides a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"different menu, the schema won’t be known in its entirety until runtime.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["// Create the dynamic schema at runtime.","let menuSchema = DynamicGenerationSchema(","    name: \"Menu\",","    properties: [","        DynamicGenerationSchema.Property(","            name: \"dailySoup\",","            schema: DynamicGenerationSchema(","                name: \"dailySoup\",","                anyOf: [\"Tomato\", \"Chicken Noodle\", \"Clam Chowder\"]","            )","        )","","        // Add additional properties.","    ]",")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"After creating a dynamic schema, use it to create a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GenerationSchema"},{"type":"text","text":""},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that you provide with your request. When you try to create a generation schema,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"it can throw an error if there are conflicting property names, undefined","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"references, or duplicate types."}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["// Create the schema.","let schema = try GenerationSchema(root: menuSchema, dependencies: [])","","// Pass the schema to the model to guide the output.","let response = try await session.respond(","    to: \"The prompt you want to make.\",","    schema: schema",")"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The response you get is an instance of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GeneratedContent","isActive":true},{"text":". You can decode the outputs","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"from schemas you define at runtime by calling "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GeneratedContent/value(_:forProperty:)-3xsez"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the property you want.","type":"text"}]}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["/documentation/foundationmodels/generating-swift-data-structures-with-guided-generation"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/technologies","doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create robust apps by describing output you want programmatically."}],"references":{"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/documentation/FoundationModels/GeneratedContent/value(_:forProperty:)-3xsez":{"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Reads a concrete "},{"code":"Generable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" type from named property."}],"identifier":"doc://com.apple.foundationmodels/docu